headline: DuPont Spinoff Qnity Started Trading Today. What to Know.
summary: A company spun out by DuPont,  Qnity Electronics  started trading on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol “Q” on Monday.  Qnity describes itself as “one of the largest global leaders in materials and solutions for the semiconductor and electronics industries,” with some 10,000 employees worldwide.  The company provides chemicals and materials used to manufacture semiconductors and circuit boards.

headline: Is Eastman Chemical a Bargain After Recent Drop and Sustainability Initiative?
summary: Ever catch yourself wondering whether Eastman Chemical stock is a diamond in the rough or just another name on your watchlist? Let's dig into what the numbers can actually tell us, especially if you're on the hunt for value. Shares have taken a noticeable hit lately, down 6.7% in the last week and 7.0% over the last month, with longer-term returns painting a more challenging picture for current holders. Market watchers have been buzzing about shifting industry dynamics and renewed attention...
